    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>ground coriander </strong>and<strong> ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> in a large bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>honey</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> and give it a good mix up until well coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken thighs </strong>to the pan and cook for 6-8 min on one side or until slightly charred</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice 1/4 of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> and cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>sugar </strong>and add your<strong> chopped dates </strong>with the <strong>sliced onion </strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> pickled onion & dates</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly chop into chunks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is charred on one side, turn the <strong>charred chicken</strong> over, then add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>onion wedges </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and cook with the lid on for 8-10 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, add your <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>remaining chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!),<strong> remaining honey </strong>and <strong>remaining lime juice</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>smoked salt </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>green harissa</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it is looking a little dry \u2013 this will help blitz the sauce!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, remove the lid and increase heat to high</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for a final 1-2 min or until all the liquid has been absorbed \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced honey chicken thigh</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-honey-chicken-thigh-with-green-harissa-yoghurt-and-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced honey chicken thigh </strong>with the<strong> rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, then the<strong> green harissa</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>pickled onion & dates</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
